<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
    <meta http-equiv="Content-type" content="text/html; charset=utf-8">
    <title>BESS Attract X Example</title>

    <script src="../../javascripts/framework.js" data-main="../../javascripts/manifest" type="text/javascript" charset="utf-8"></script>

	<link href="../../prettify/prettify.css" rel="stylesheet" />
	<link href="../../stylesheets/examples.css" rel="stylesheet" />
	<link href="../../besheets/examples.bess" type="text/bess" />
	
	<style type="text/css" media="screen">
		#clickr:hover {
			cursor: pointer;
		}

		#two div{
			position: relative;
			background-color: #f0f0f0;
			border: 1px solid black;
		}

		#two{
			padding: 0px; /* Correct 1em that is global for examples, but screws up this calc... */
		}

	</style>

</head>
<body>
<h2>attractX</h2>

<div class="e">
	<p>Attracts one element (the left property) along the X axis in relation to another element .</p>
	<pre class="source prettyprint"></pre>
	<div class="sample">
		<style type="text/bess">
			#two a:nth(0):clicked{
				effect-target:     where('#b');
				effect-name:       'attractX';
				effect-relative:   to('#a');
			}

			#two a:nth(1):clicked{
				effect-target:     where('#b');
				effect-name:       'attractX';
				effect-relative:   to('#c');
			}
		</style>
		<div class="example" id="two" style="position:relative;">
			<div id="a" style="left: 300px;width: 100px;">Element A</div>

			<div id="b" style="width: 300px;">Element B <br /> <a href=="#">Attract to A</a> <br /> <a href=="#">Attract to C</a></div>

			<div id="c" style="left: 600px;width: 100px;">Element C</div>
		</div>
	</div>
</div>



</body>
</html>